The extendable back has rubber wrapping so it will not move. There are also four rubber feet to prevent slippage while protecting your sink and counter from scratches.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sits Perfectly In My Sink
reviews.reviewText: I was so tired of having a dish drainer that took up space on my granite countertop. My husband is a builder and said that new sinks now come with a sit-in sink drainer. I thought I would try this one to see if I would be happy. It is perfect. I do not have many things I need to hand wash, but it works for my pots and pans and any other hand washable items. I highly recommend this item.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect size for my new sink
reviews.reviewText: When we put in a new sink, we needed to get a new dish rack as our other one would not fit. This one fits perfectly as it is adjustable, which I love and it looks great. It holds the dishes, glassware, and even pans very well. It seems very sturdy and super easy to adjust to the sink size.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Well construcuted and useful-with one caveat.....
reviews.reviewText: This product is well designed, likely not stainless steel as advertised, but chrome plated. It fits well in a traditional sink, and many users will not use the expandable facets of this strainer. The rubber on the expandable arms is a nice feature. Be aware-that the utensil holder is only secured by two points. Placing larger untensils, or too many utensils in the holder will cause it to "flip away" scattering your items in the sink or onto the floor. This is easily fixed by making a hole in the bottom and adding a cable tie-but this prevents the holder from being removed for washing. In a larger sink, the holder can be mounted on the outside of the strainer, creating more room for items to dry. Overall-a good product, but not perfect.
